result.name: Xin Yi Restaurant

reviews.text:
Another indistinguishable Cha Chaan Teng that serve breakfast, lunch and dinner at different time.  This is one of the rare ones that opens 24 hours in Shatin area.

Foodwise pretty much same as all others, tasted mediocre and price ranges similar: breakfast $30-40 range, lunch 40-50, dinner 60 and up for set meals.

Service in here are non-existing, speed and efficiency usually is the norm in this genre of restaurant.  On this visit the waiter was actually borderline rude.

One thing about service in general in HK, I wish there's more smiles.  I don't know, maybe having the most expensive housing in the world put a frown on most people's faces.
Rude service with poor manner and waiters with dirty hands. The food is ok, but will not go again next time.
Cheap & tasty! 24hr open
